title.rendered: Pakistan Women vs Sri Lanka Women, 3rd T20I: Today’s Match Preview, Fantasy Cricket Tips

content.rendered:
We have opted for a fantasy cricket team based on the recent performances, overall impact, and credit points.

Pitch Report

In both games, Sri Lanka got bundled out under 110. It was a result of poor shot selection against quality spinners. Given the way Pakistan have batted, it does not prove that the pitch has demons.

Teams

Probable XI for Pakistan: Muneeba Ali (wk), Gull Feroza, Iram Javed, Bismah Maroof (c), Nida Dar, Aliya Riaz, Ayesha Naseem, Fatima Sana, Tuba Hassan, Aiman Anwer, Anam Amin

Probable XI for Sri Lanka: Chamari Athapaththu (c), Hasini Perera, Harshitha Madavi (wk), Nilakshi de Silva, Anushka Sanjeewani, Kavisha Dilhari, Ama Kanchana, Oshadi Ranasinghe, Inoka Ranaweera, Sugandika Kumari, Achini Kulasuriya

Power Players

Tuba Hossain has collected the most fantasy points (60) on My11Circle. She followed her match-winning bowling figures of 3 for 8 with 1 for 13 in the second game. Sri Lanka have been finding it difficult to negotiate her leg-break.

The same has been the case with the slow left-arm orthodox of Anam Amin. She has taken 4 wickets at an average of 9.2.

Bismah Maroof was instrumental with the bat in both games. She has scores of 28* and 22 to her name. Sri Lanka has not been scoring enough runs for Bismah to score more.

Smart Picks

Ayesha Naseem went all guns blazing the moment she took the crease. The result was a blistering knock of 45* off 31 including five fours and six.

Chamari Athapaththu has scored in single digits in consecutive games. Before the series, she was in spectacular form. She was the highest run-scorer in the Invitation League: 313 runs at a strike rate of 139 in 7 games.

Hasini Perera top scored with 35 runs in the second T20I, but it came at the cost of 51 deliveries. Sri Lanka kept losing wickets at the other end and Hasini had no option but to occupy the crease.

Nilakshi de Silva has scored the bulk of the runs for Sri Lanka. Her last five competitive scores read 23*, 49*, 28, 25, and 21.

Of all the Sri Lankan bowlers, Oshadi Ranasinghe has performed the best. She has taken 3 wickets and maintained an economy of 5.5

Match Preview

Pakistan have already sealed the series 2-0. Given they have chased in both games, they will look to bat first in case they win the toss. 

Time: May 28, 7:30 PM
